items.text:
Registry build order: (1) registry.draft.create → get draft_id. (2) registry.meta.set — title and description. (3) Ask whether memory is needed. (4) registry.section.add_item for base_context. (5) personas. (6) sentiment. (7) output_prompt_directions. (8) static/runtime injections if needed. (9) memory_recall section — add item with id='recall', text='{memory_recall}', template_vars=['memory_recall'] (only when memory is enabled). (10) prompt_endings — IMPORTANT: if memory is enabled, prompt_endings MUST include template_vars ['system_summary', 'rule_ending'] and the item text MUST contain {system_summary} and {rule_ending}; use format: '{system_summary}

{rule_ending}
' plus any chat-prefix items. (11) registry.assembly.set_order — use 'prompt_endings.endings' (not .text); include 'memory_recall.text' when memory is enabled. (12) registry.generation.set if needed. (13) registry.memory.configure + registry.classifier_rule.add if memory is enabled — memory.configure accepts: top_k, history_window, emotional_state_enabled, emotion_dimensions (array), emotion_decay_rate, working_notes_enabled, system_summary_enabled, use_classifier, classifier_chat_path. Classifier rule actions MUST use format: [{"type": "emotion", "deltas": {"dimension": float}}] — never use 'emotion_delta', 'dimension' key, or 'delta' key. (14) registry.draft.validate — explain all errors. (15) registry.draft.export when ready. HARD RULES: NEVER call registry.output_policy.set — it does not belong in built registries. NEVER create a user_message section — it is runtime-only. Proceed through this order one step at a time, only on user directive.
